@NODE Introduction


	                       INTRODUCTION


	This program is for detecting the largest variety of musicformats 
	available for the AMIGAź. Detection is possible in both a dynamic
	buffer  you can read any data to  and  in specified  valid system
	memory ranges. At the moment a total of 82 different sound@{"formats" LINK Soundformats}
	can be detected.ExoticRipperź offers a CLI like console interface
	to the user.  If the @{"Reqtools Library" LINK Copyrights} is present in LIBS: reading
        and writing checkdata or modules is performed  via filerequesters.
	ALWAYS REMEMBER: ExoticRipperź is no brain replacement project!
	The authors take no responsibility in breaking your machine.

	ExoticRipper'sź aim is to make you 
	boldly hear what no man has heard before...


@ENDNODE

